product_name: DiorForever Skin Perfect 24H Multi-Use Foundation Stick
summary: SummaryDior's innovative multi-use Forever Skin Perfect Stick that delivers a natural, blurred finish, 24h* coverage, and all-day hydration.**
details: DetailsBenefitsThis buildable coverage Dior foundation stick glides over the skin to even out your complexion and visibly eliminate imperfections in a single sweep. Delivering a "blurring filter" effect that resists heat and humidity, the stick can be used as a foundation, concealer or for touch-ups on the go.FeaturesMatte, BuildableItem 2629086How To UseFOUNDATION: Apply directly to the cheeks, nose, forehead and chin with the flat part of the oval and then blend using the fingertips, a face brush or a beauty blender.CONCEALER: Apply the stick on areas requiring correction, then blend using the fingertips, face brush or a beauty blender.TOUCH-UPS: Apply the stick over the course of the day.Ingredients0 N Neutral: C15-19 Alkane, Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride, Mica, Helianthus Annuus (Sunflower) Seed Wax, Saccharomyces Ferment, Coco-Caprylate/Caprate, Silica, Phytosteryl/Octyldodecyl Lauroyl Glutamate, Polyglyceryl-2 Triisostearate, Iris Florentina Root Extract, Aluminum Hydroxide, Parfum (Fragrance), Brassica Campestris (Rapeseed) Seed Oil, Candelilla Cera (Euphorbia Cerifera (Candelilla) Wax), Cera Carnauba (Copernicia Cerifera (Carnauba) Wax), Lauroyl Lysine, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Opuntia Ficus-Indica Flower Extract, Camelina Sativa Seed Oil, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, Aqua (Water), Tocopherol, Sodium Benzoate, Potassium Sorbate. May Contain: CI 77891 (Titanium Dioxide), CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499 (Iron Oxides).Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: FOUNDATION: Apply directly to the cheeks, nose, forehead and chin with the flat part of the oval and then blend using the fingertips, a face brush or a beauty blender.CONCEALER: Apply the stick on areas requiring correction, then blend using the fingertips, face brush or a beauty blender.TOUCH-UPS: Apply the stick over the course of the day.

reviews.headline: Found the one that I'll buy over and over again.

reviews.headline: Biggest BUYERS Regret
reviews.comments: This has got to be the WORST foundation ever. You could literally see every dry patch on my skin and made it look EXTRA dry. Even in places I couldn't see without the foundation being applied. It always has a funeral makeup look to it after applied. I hate it and have drugstore foundations a 1/3 of the price that work a look much better than this. This is just so bad. NEVER again.

reviews.headline: So Sad
reviews.comments:
I'll start by saying this is the best foundation stick I've tried (out of Ilia, Hourglass, LYS and ABH). It's creamy, gliding around the skin and blending like a dream. This has a natural finish with medium coverage. It's also a lightweight formula, and I didn't feel like I was wearing anything. 

There is a perfumey scent that I don't mind, but someone who is sensitive to fragrances may not enjoy. Also, the shade range is abysmal. I'm very fair cool (shade Oslo in NARS) and the 1CR is almost a shade and a half too dark. 

Overall, I love the product for someone with moisturized base and light to medium skin tones. It definitely lived up to the hype, im just sad not even my tan self will be able to use it.

reviews.headline: Compact
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] It was too dark for me so I had to give it to my sister. She said she likes the matte finish and how compact it was. The packaging is sleek and easy for on the go. Could be full coverage if layered but good for light natural look days as well.

reviews.headline: The best
reviews.comments: I absolutely love this stick!

reviews.headline: Best Dior foundation
reviews.comments: I haven't bought a Dior foundation since they discontinued the Airflash spray foundation. This foundation just slide and melts into your skin, so easy to blend. Love it!

reviews.headline: Heavily Perfumed!!!!
reviews.comments: I never had a foundation that has so much perfume that it gives you a headache and it stays with you all day. Perfume goes on your body not on your face.  It's too bad because the shade was perfect.  So expensive but so dumb of them to add perfume.

reviews.headline: I had high hopes!
reviews.comments: I wanted to love this so bad! It slides on nice but it sticks on to every semi dry skin patch you have, even it wasn't able to be seen by the naked eye before. Also infele like it accentuated my pores which is the opposite of what I want. I tried it over primer also. That made it semi better but not much. I also dont want to work that hard to like a foundation. I like looking "your skin but better". I don't like to look cakey. Its going back :/

reviews.headline: Luxury
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This item is amazing quality. From the packaging, smooth application, density of color and the formula spreads so nicely. This color was dark for my skin tone so used it as a bronzer stick & love.

reviews.headline: Yes a million times
reviews.comments: I am not a luxury makeup person, but there are a few items that I will splurge on. This is one of them. Blends like a dream. I have combo to oily skin (and live in a very hot and humid climate), and this foundation lasted all day on me. Blends so easily, gives a beautiful finish, what else can I say. I'm not a big fan of the scent, but the product is so good that I don't care. Yes, I did use a mattifying primer andoose powder... I do that with all of my makeup.

reviews.headline: Go buy rn
reviews.comments: I absolutely love this foundation stick, it has such a nice coverage and is so beginner friendly. If you struggle with acne this is wonderful as well.

faceoff_positive.comments:
Shade Name: 1 N Neutral  Very light with neutral undertones.

Actual Shade: Closer to a light-tan, cool-toned neutral. This is not a fair or lighter skin shade and it does not directly correspond to what is typically expected from a 1N shade in other brands. For reference, I usually wear a Glossier G11 or a Make Up For Ever Y225 and this shade is NOT a color match for those. 

Undertone: Shade 1 leans towards a peachy undertone with cool-toned elements. 

Color Depth: Despite expectations based on numbering, Shade 1N appears to be a darker shade than 1.5N due to its undertone. This shade may be better suited for someone with the lightest "tan" skin tone because of its deeper, peachy hue. I would say that Dior's 1N may reach up to 2.5x darker than your average 1N shade. 

Swatch Recommendation: 
- The product looks different on the skin than how it appears in the tube.
- Swatch in person. Test on your face and neck, not your just on your wrist or hand. Test on spots of redness and on your T-Zone to know for sure if a cool-toned neutral is right for you. Compare it against your neck to see if it looks too dark.
- Swatch directly on your neck if you struggle to see tone differences in various lighting situations.

Consistency:The Dior foundation sticks are of a medium to thick consistency, yet are still soft, creamy, and ultra-blendable. 

Scent: 
The foundation has a subtle scent of blooming iris flowers that I found to be very refreshing and pleasant. I personally love that they're scented, as it adds that extra luxurious touch that you don't often see brands bother with. My combo-dry skin didn't experience any sensitivity or irritation from the added scent ingredients. 

Full coverage:
These foundation sticks are marketed as buildable to full coverage, but I personally found that it's far too easy to reach that full-coverage point and end up accidentally applying too much product onto the skin. 

Application: 
Resist the urge to draw bold lines across every section of your face!

To avoid a cakey, stage-makeup-like appearance, I recommend using spread-out dots that are few in number. Spot dabbing and blending out the product resulted in the most beautiful, natural-looking skin with a luminous or satin finish. This method works particularly well for me, as I have combination-dry skin and prefer a more natural look.
faceoff_positive.headline: The numbering/undertone scale is off

faceoff_negative.comments:
I received this product for free to review. 

I've never tried a foundation stick before let alone a high end one. The packaging is simple and luxe, it's on the heavier side and it snaps closed. As with high end products, this does have a scent which fades once you put it on but I still think it's unnecessary to have scented makeup. The formula itself is easy to spread, but it is slightly thick. I could tell right away that it was not the best color match but that doesn't affect my opinion. Blending it out was fine and the coverage is a little more than sheer. I applied it a couple of different ways both times straight on to the skin with the stick but I tried once to blend with my sponge and then with a brush. The time with the sponge looked a little better blended out than with a brush. I wore this three times, once without primer, once with primer & again without. On my skin, it lasted a good 6 hours without the primer, as I usually wear face makeup without it, before it started to look a little cakey. With primer, it seemed to stay a little more but not much. Everyone's skin is different so your mileage may vary there. Overall, I don't think this converted me into a stick foundation person and it's not a favorite, it's just average. If you can test it in store, then it's worth checking out.
faceoff_negative.headline: High end foundation stick
